cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM

Reasoning: The paper deals with modeling human sense of relationships between objects based on their appearance, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves developing a scalable method for uncovering human notions of visual relationships, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) the second likely sub-category. The paper also deals with developing a system capable of recommending which clothes and accessories will go well together, which involves recommendation systems and machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the third likely sub-category. The paper also involves network inference and graph-based modeling, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia), making them the fourth and fifth likely sub-categories, respectively.
